title: ‘Toxic groom’: MAFS bachelor slammed for not wanting a woke, ugly wife
description: Sky News host Freya Leach questions why the Married at First Sight bachelor has been slammed for wanting traditional values in his wife.  “This season they have a new bachelor on the show,” Ms Leach said.   “The Sydney Morning Herald has labelled him as a toxic groom.  “He wants to be a provider and a protector, and he doesn’t want a woke, ugly wife; what’s so wrong with that?”

title: Hillary Clinton testifies she has ‘no knowledge’ to assist Epstein investigation
description: Hillary Clinton is appearing before the US House Oversight Committee as part of its investigation into the late sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.  She testified before the committee, “you have compelled me to testify, fully aware that I have no knowledge that would assist your investigation”.  Ms Clinton said her appearance would “distract attention from President Trump’s actions”.

title: Iran-US talks underway in Geneva to avert major conflict
description: Talks between the US and Iran are currently underway in Geneva to avert a major conflict.  The US has built up military forces around the Middle East, but claims it wants to find a diplomatic solution.  The discussions briefly paused but have since resumed.

title: Dems pushing to ‘hurt’ Trump with Epstein dig despite the left looking ‘worse’ off
description: Republican strategist John Jordan says the Democrats are pushing to hurt Trump despite the left looking worse off by the Epstein scandal.  “Democrats keep pushing this Epstein thing as if it’s going to hurt Trump for reasons that I just can’t fathom,” Mr Jordan told Sky News Australia.  “The more it goes on, the worse it gets for the left, but for whatever reason, they just keep wanting to dig in this.”

title: Shadow Treasurer Tim Wilson heckled at Goldstein community event
description: The Shadow Treasurer Tim Wilson has been interrupted at a community event in his electorate of Goldstein.  The hecklers interrupted the event to confront the Shadow Treasurer over crime and immigration.  Mr Wilson posted on X, “Unfortunately, it’s been a distressing evening”.

title: ‘Happy to talk’: Joyce open to Coalition deal to achieve conservative ‘policy outcomes’
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce claims both One Nation and the Coalition will need to help each other with preference deals.  “Both of us will require a preference deal of some sort,” Mr Joyce told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “We’re not looking for ministerial positions, we’re looking for outcomes in policy.  “We are happy to be conservative, we’re not embarrassed about that, and if other people on the same political side want to talk with us, well, we’re happy to talk with them.”

title: Bill Clinton would’ve preferred to ‘avoid’ testifying over Epstein to US committee
description: Republican strategist John Jordan claims Bill Clinton would’ve “avoided” testifying before the US House Oversight Committee over Jeffrey Epstein if he “could have”.  “Hillary Clinton and Bill Clinton are different animals with regard to Epstein,” Mr Jordan told Sky News Australia.  “When there is a congressional subpoena, you have to testify; otherwise, you're subject to prosecution.  “If Bill Clinton could have avoided testifying, believe me, he would have.”

title: North Korea puts on military parade to show its arsenal
description: North Korea has put on a show of military force in its capital Pyongyang.  14,000 troops marched through the main square in a nighttime parade.  Kim Jong Un used his closing speech to double down on expanding North Korea’s nuclear arsenal.

title: Trump-Mamdani ‘productive’ meeting results in release of Colombian student detained by ICE
description: US President Donald Trump and New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani have met at the White House again.  Mr Mamdani described the meeting as “productive” and is looking forward to building more housing in New York City.  The New York City Mayor also used the meeting to share his concerns about a Colombian student detained by ICE.

title: Hillary Clinton insists she has ‘never been’ to Epstein’s island in explosive grilling
description: Sky News Washington Correspondent Jonathan Kearsley says Hillary Clinton insisted she had “never been to Epstein’s island”.  Hillary Clinton has been questioned for hours on what she knew about Jeffrey Epstein’s crimes in a closed-door committee.  Ms Clinton delivered an explosive opening statement, calling on them to question US President Donald Trump.

title: ASX set to move modestly higher with index futures up 0.1 per cent
description: CommSec’s James Gruber claims the ASX is set to move modestly higher today with index futures up 0.1 per cent.  “The ASX is set to move modestly higher with index futures up 0.1 per cent,” Mr Gruber told Sky News Australia.  “That’s despite a slump on Wall Street.”  Presented by CommSec.

title: ‘I never met Epstein’: Hillary Clinton speaks after testifying to US committee
description: Former US secretary of state Hillary Clinton claims she “never met" Jeffrey Epstein after testifying to the US House Oversight Committee.

title: Lefties Losing It: Democrats crash out all week as America wins big
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi has reacted to Democrats crash out all week as America wins big.

title: ‘Short, sharp and violent’: Potential US strike on Iran will be destructive for the regime
description: Former Home Affairs secretary Mike Pezzullo says a potential US strike on Iran will be “short, sharp and violent”.

title: ‘Narcissists’: Harry and Meghan help ‘garner sympathy’ with Middle East visit
description: Stepmates Studios’ Mark Nicholson claims Prince Harry and Meghan are “narcissists” amid their visit to a refugee camp in Jordan.  “These refugees, they've been handed it – they’ve had a rough trot,” Mr Nicholson told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “But they have garnered more sympathy in the last 24 hours for spending an afternoon with these two narcissists.”
